<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - VALVE TRAIN: CAMSHAFT, HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTERS AND PUSH RODS -
        HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTER ROLLER TYPE - Reassembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Reassembly</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk document="e435_65.xml" xrefid="ef4350402">4.2</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            .
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat all hydraulic valve lifter parts with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install plunger spring and plunger into lifter body.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install metering valve and push rod seat into lifter, install retaining ring.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>After reassembly, perform a leakdown test to assure that leakage past the plunger and cylinder
                        is correct and to assure that the check valve is functioning properly.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
